'''Sri Sri Radha Banke Bihari Ji Mandir''', generally known as the '''[[ISKCON]] Patna Temple''', is the upcoming temple on Buddha Marg in [[Patna]], [[India]].

The construction of temple was started in 2007 and is expected to be completed by 2017<ref>{{cite web | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/patna/Rs-51cr-ISKCON-temple-coming-up-in-Patna/articleshow/46328273.cms | title=Rs 51cr ISKCON temple coming up in Patna | publisher=The Times of India | date=22 February 2015 | accessdate=25 February 2015}}</ref> with an estimated budget of {{INRConvert|51|c}}.<ref name="indiatimes">{{cite web | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/patna/ISKCON-temple-at-Patna-to-be-completed-by-2014/articleshow/14481077.cms | title=ISKCON temple at Patna to be completed by 2014 - The Times of India | publisher=Timesofindia.indiatimes.com | date=2012-06-29 | accessdate=2014-05-01}}</ref> When completed, it will be the largest building in Patna and also the largest Radha Krishna temple in the entire [[Bihar]] and [[Jharkhand]] region.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1110628/jsp/bihar/story_14166261.jsp |title=Iskcon temple in two years |publisher=Telegraphindia.com |date=2011-06-28 |accessdate=2014-05-01}}</ref> Spread over an area of over 2 acres, the temple will have 84 pillars.<ref name="indiatimes" /> It will contain the altars of three deities, namely, ''Sri Sri Gaur Nitai'',
''Sri Sri Radha Banke Bihari Ji'' and ''Sri Sri Ram Durbar''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://iskconpatna.com/iskpat.php |title=Glory of Bihar - &#124; |publisher=Iskcon Patna |date= |accessdate=2014-05-01}}</ref>

